			<li>Focusing on activities that deliver sales.</li>
			<li>Every participant will leave with specific steps on how to success.</li>
		</ul>
		<h2 class="topics-sub">MANAGEMENT</h2>
		<h2 class="subheading">One to One Management - Managing/Motivating Individuals</h2>
		<p class="dynamic-p">Today's business environment means managing and motivating employees is more important than ever. Sean's philosophy is that your people must be your top priority. By hiring the best, inspiring the best, and keeping the best, other company objectives fall in line. Sean urges his managers to focus on individuals and to set specific motivation strategies for each person. As a result his company consistently has double digit growth while maintaining single digit employee turnover.</p>
		<ul class="topics-ul">
			<li>The best teams have the best players - How to get them on your team.</li>
			<li>How to Hire, Inspire,and Fire for maximum results.</li>
			<li>How to inspire everyone from the all-star to the role player.</li>
			<li>Why eliminating poor performance is important to everyone.</li>
			<li>Specifics your managers will use today!</li>
		</ul>
		<h2 class="topics-sub">STRATEGY</h2>
		<h2 class="subheading">The X Strategy - For maximum growth!</h2>
		<p class="dynamic-p">If you are seeking rapid growth, the X strategy is the way to get it! Surpassing $100 million in sales in less than 5 years, and doubling soon after, did not happen by accident for Sean's company. Sean shares his strategy secrets in a unique approach for finding market opportunities and determining where, and how, to attack the competition.</p>
		<ul class="topics-ul">
			<li>The strategy when significant growth is the goal.</li>
			<li>A sure fire way to turn your largest prospect into your best customer!</li>
			<li>Why doing the "opposite" works better than following the pack.</li>
			<li>Where to attack and how to do it.</li>
			<li>Examples of how others turned ideas into multi-million dollar sales.</li>
			<li>A Step by Step process for finding the right opportunity and attacking it.</li>
		</ul>
